The paper deals with the problem of graph clustering, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the LambdaPrime objective, which is related to other parameterized clustering problems, such as modularity, and captures specific clustering problems as special cases. This suggests that the paper may also fall under the categories of social and information networks (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also uses linear programming and approximation algorithms, which are techniques commonly used in the field of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and theoretical computer science (cs.CC).
